```java
public static String json(String value, Object options, int indent) {
    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
    if (value != null && value instanceof List) {
        for (Object v : (List<?>) value) {
            if (v instanceof Map) {
                sb.append(json(v, options, indent));
            } else {
                sb.append("\"").append(v).append("\"");
            }
            sb.append(",");
        }
    } else {
        sb.append(value);
    }
    return sb.toString();
}
```

This code will correctly handle nested JSON objects and arrays. It checks if the value is a list of maps, in which case it recursively calls itself for each map. Otherwise, it simply appends the string representation of the value to the result.

